

<section>
  <title>exercises</title>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        Use Newton's Method to compute the root of each of the following
        functions, using the given initial guess.
        <ul>
          <li>
            <title>(a)</title>
            <p>
              <m>f(x)=x-2,\\ \text{ Guess: }  a=5</m>
            </p>
          </li>

          <li>
            <title>(b)</title>
            <p>
              <m>f(x)=x^2-2,\\ \text{ Guess: }  a=5</m>
            </p>
          </li>

          <li>
            <title>(c)</title>
            <p>
              <m>f(x)=x^3-2,\\ \text{ Guess: }  a=5</m>
            </p>
          </li>

          <li>
            <title>(d)</title>
            <p>
              <m>f(x)=x-5,\\ \text{ Guess: }  a=2</m>
            </p>
          </li>

          <li>
            <title>(e)</title>
            <p>
              <m>f(x)=x^2-5,\\ \text{ Guess: }  a=2</m>
            </p>
          </li>

          <li>
            <title>(f)</title>
            <p>
              <m>f(x)=x^3-5,\\ \text{ Guess: }  a=2</m>
            </p>
          </li>

          <li>
            <title>(g)</title>
            <p>
              <m>f(x)=x+7,\\ \text{ Guess: }  a=0</m>
            </p>
          </li>

          <li>
            <title>(h)</title>
            <p>
              <m>f(x)=x^2+7,\\ \text{ Guess: }  a=0</m>
            </p>
          </li>

          <li>
            <title>(i)</title>
            <p>
              <m>f(x)=x^3-7,\\ \text{ Guess: }  a=0</m>
            </p>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </p>
    </statement>
  </exercise>
  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        Suppose that a cubic polynomial has three real roots, that two
        of them, <m>r_1</m> and <m>r_2</m> are known, and we wish to approximate the
        third. Show that if we take the average of <m>r_1</m> and <m>r_2</m> as our
        initial guess, Newton's Method will find the third root exactly in
        one iteration.
      </p>
    </statement>
  </exercise>
</section>

